<section class="what-is-radon">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-column">
        <h2>What is Radon?</h2>
        <p class="lead">Radon is a colorless, odorless, radioactive gas that occurs naturally when uranium in soil, rock, and water breaks down. It's the second leading cause of lung cancer in the United States.</p>
        
        <div class="radon-facts">
          <div class="fact-card">
            <h3>How Radon Enters Your Home</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Cracks in foundation walls and floors</li>
              <li>Gaps around service pipes</li>
              <li>Construction joints</li>
              <li>Well water (in some cases)</li>
              <li>Building materials (rare)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="fact-card">
            <h3>Health Risks</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Lung cancer (even in non-smokers)</li>
              <li>Increased risk for smokers</li>
              <li>Long-term exposure effects</li>
              <li>No immediate symptoms</li>
              <li>Silent health threat</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="visual-column">
        <div class="radon-levels-chart">
          <h3>EPA Radon Action Levels</h3>
          <div class="level-bar safe">
            <span class="level-number">0-2 pCi/L</span>
            <span class="level-status">Safe Level</span>
          </div>
          <div class="level-bar caution">
            <span class="level-number">2-4 pCi/L</span>
            <span class="level-status">Consider Mitigation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="level-bar danger">
            <span class="level-number">4+ pCi/L</span>
            <span class="level-status">Action Required</span>
          </div>
          <div class="level-bar critical">
            <span class="level-number">20+ pCi/L</span>
            <span class="level-status">Immediate Action</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
